      "content": {
        "headerTitle": "Fair Debt Collection Practices Act (1977)",
        "layout": "concept-full",
        "layoutData": {
          "title": "Protection from Abusive Debt Collectors",
          "paragraphs": [
            "The FDCPA eliminates abusive practices by third-party debt collectors. It establishes clear rules for how, when, and where collectors can contact you.",
            "Call before 8 AM or after 9 PM, use threats or profanity, claim to be attorneys (unless true), contact you at work if told not to",
            "Identify themselves, provide written debt verification within 5 days, stop contacting you if you request in writing",
            "<strong>Key Right:</strong> You can request debt validation. The collector must prove you owe the debt before continuing collection attempts."
          ],
          "bulletPoints": []
        }
